00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:03,354
THIS DRAMA IS PURELY FICTIONAL
AND IS NOT ASSOCIATED WITH

2
00:01:03,438 --> 00:01:05,982
ACTUAL PEOPLE, PARTIES, LOCATIONS,
CORPORATIONS OR INCIDENTS

3
00:01:06,066 --> 00:01:12,072
10 YEARS AGO

4
00:01:12,739 --> 00:01:14,240
Why did you apply for this position?

5
00:01:15,617 --> 00:01:17,118
It's better to join the police.

6
00:01:18,495 --> 00:01:21,206
There's no pension,
and it's a contract position.

7
00:01:21,873 --> 00:01:23,291
Because I want to change the world.

8
00:01:29,214 --> 00:01:32,133
Look at you making such a cheesy remark
without even batting an eye.

9
00:01:32,634 --> 00:01:35,345
Doesn't it make you cringe
when you say things like that?

10
00:01:38,306 --> 00:01:39,432
No, because I mean it.

11
00:01:46,231 --> 00:01:47,982
5 YEARS AGO
SECRETARY, JANG TAE-JUN

12
00:01:48,066 --> 00:01:49,859
You can refer to this. Like this.

13
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:51,361
Just check this part.

14
00:01:53,071 --> 00:01:54,280
Got it, sir.

15
00:02:06,334 --> 00:02:07,377
ASSEMBLYMAN LEE JONG-DAE

16
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:12,257
You call this a speech?

17
00:02:13,258 --> 00:02:14,425
Rewrite the whole thing.

18
00:02:15,802 --> 00:02:17,679
Train him well, for God's sake.

19
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:30,275
You see...

20
00:02:30,942 --> 00:02:33,611
You're doing a great job,
so don't be discouraged.

21
00:02:34,279 --> 00:02:36,865
It's just that Assemblyman Lee
can't see the potential in you yet.

22
00:02:38,783 --> 00:02:40,618
I heard you received an offer

23
00:02:41,703 --> 00:02:44,706
from Assemblyman Song's office
to join them as the Chief of Staff.

24
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:48,710
Yes, I did.

25
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:51,087
That man, Mr. Song...

26
00:02:51,671 --> 00:02:54,007
Everything he does irks me,

27
00:02:54,090 --> 00:02:56,759
but he has such a keen eye for talent.
I've got to give him that.

28
00:02:57,260 --> 00:03:00,555
You got an offer from a big shot
in one of the opposition parties,

29
00:03:00,972 --> 00:03:02,682
so you should be proud of yourself.

30
00:03:03,683 --> 00:03:04,976
You're all grown up now.

31
00:03:09,397 --> 00:03:11,608
What about you?
When will you join the Assembly?

32
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:17,488
You should start preparing for it.

33
00:03:18,823 --> 00:03:20,283
I should give it a shot next year.

34
00:03:20,366 --> 00:03:22,202
I see.

35
00:03:23,161 --> 00:03:24,662
Do you have someone who can help you?

36
00:03:26,706 --> 00:03:27,624
I'll start looking.

37
00:03:30,084 --> 00:03:31,628
So when are you joining Mr. Song's office?

38
00:03:31,711 --> 00:03:32,962
Well...

39
00:03:34,464 --> 00:03:37,467
How can I go anywhere when I know
all you can do is poke your nose

40
00:03:37,592 --> 00:03:38,927
into other people's business?

41
00:03:39,135 --> 00:03:41,763
Even when I'm here looking after you,
I'm still worried about you.

42
00:03:50,521 --> 00:03:51,648
What's with that look?

43
00:03:53,107 --> 00:03:55,276
I guess you weren't planning on taking me.

44
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:57,445
Fine. Forget it, then.

45
00:03:57,612 --> 00:03:59,822
I guess I counted my chickens
before they were hatched.

46
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:04,077
Forget it.
Don't take me if you don't want to.

47
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:05,828
Goodness.

48
00:04:06,412 --> 00:04:07,372
Gosh.

49
00:04:11,084 --> 00:04:12,377
I'm touched.

50
00:04:16,214 --> 00:04:17,757
What are you doing?

51
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:19,801
Seriously? Look at me.

52
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:21,928
What the hell?

53
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,807
I'm not crying.
It's just that the chili is spicy.

54
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:30,478
Come on. What are you doing now?

55
00:04:38,528 --> 00:04:39,612
Seong-min.

56
00:04:41,030 --> 00:04:41,906
Both you

57
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:44,117
and I...

58
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:48,329
should get elected as an assemblyman
with a badge on our chest

59
00:04:48,746 --> 00:04:50,832
and walk in there triumphantly!

60
00:04:51,749 --> 00:04:54,836
A fair, corruption-free nation!

61
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:57,964
A country
where all of its people can prosper!

62
00:04:58,047 --> 00:05:00,717
Let's work together
to create such a world!

63
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:03,386
Yes!

64
00:05:04,721 --> 00:05:05,888
Like you said,

65
00:05:06,597 --> 00:05:09,309
let's make a change in this world!

66
00:05:09,392 --> 00:05:12,603
-Let's make a change!
-Let's make a change!

67
00:05:12,687 --> 00:05:14,772
Let's make a change!

68
00:05:15,732 --> 00:05:17,567
Stuck in a place
where the skies can't be seen

69
00:05:18,609 --> 00:05:20,945
while having to fight against time
that can't be measured,

70
00:05:21,612 --> 00:05:25,742
you must push the rock upward
so that it doesn't fall down the hill.

71
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:31,914
My apologies, sir.

72
00:05:37,086 --> 00:05:39,547
To survive in this disgusting world,

73
00:05:39,922 --> 00:05:41,299
I had to lower my head

74
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:43,259
and swallow my pride.

75
00:05:48,973 --> 00:05:50,641
It's about time you were introduced.

76
00:05:51,726 --> 00:05:52,643
I...

77
00:05:53,019 --> 00:05:53,936
Come in.

78
00:05:59,525 --> 00:06:01,110
Hey, Mr. Jang.

79
00:06:04,364 --> 00:06:05,406
Hello.

80
00:06:06,532 --> 00:06:07,700
I am Jang Tae-jun.

81
00:06:08,618 --> 00:06:12,830
Just like that,
I managed to climb up the ladder.

82
00:06:25,676 --> 00:06:27,804
With my dogged persistence and tenacity,
I survived.

83
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:32,934
However, there is nothing

84
00:06:34,227 --> 00:06:35,686
in my hands now.

85
00:06:52,245 --> 00:06:55,331
EPISODE 8

86
00:06:56,999 --> 00:07:00,878
If Iâ€™m given the opportunity to serve
as the Minister of Justice,

87
00:07:01,337 --> 00:07:04,048
I will work hard to serve my country
and its people

88
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:06,509
in the best way that I can.

89
00:07:07,677 --> 00:07:08,678
Thank you.

90
00:07:12,557 --> 00:07:14,392
Mr. Ahn is one of Mr. Song's closest men.

91
00:07:14,475 --> 00:07:17,687
He wouldn't have added this question
without discussing it with Mr. Song.

92
00:07:17,979 --> 00:07:19,647
Your name is mentioned here.

93
00:07:19,856 --> 00:07:21,983
It's weird enough
that Mr. Lee got picked as a witness.

94
00:07:22,066 --> 00:07:25,027
They're trying to blame you
for all the suspicions regarding Mr. Song.

95
00:07:26,404 --> 00:07:29,323
They're going to make it seem like
it was all your own personal doing.

96
00:07:33,161 --> 00:07:34,579
We will now accept questions

97
00:07:34,745 --> 00:07:37,373
for the Minister of Justice nominee.

98
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:39,876
Each committee member will have

99
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:43,796
up to seven minutes to ask the questions
that they have prepared.

100
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:46,924
This confirmation hearing
is being broadcast live,

101
00:07:47,008 --> 00:07:49,927
so please make sure
you don't exceed your speaking time.

102
00:07:50,011 --> 00:07:53,139
Assemblyman Ahn Hyeon-min,
you may go ahead.

103
00:07:53,431 --> 00:07:55,141
I'm Ahn Hyeon-min from the Daehan Party.

104
00:07:55,224 --> 00:07:58,186
First and foremost,
congratulations on your nomination.

105
00:07:58,853 --> 00:07:59,854
Thank you.

106
00:08:00,563 --> 00:08:03,274
From what I've observed over the years,
I know that the candidate

107
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:04,734
always does his best

108
00:08:04,942 --> 00:08:07,403
to protect the law
and never compromise his morals.

109
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:10,031
I asked many people's opinions
while preparing for this hearing,

110
00:08:10,114 --> 00:08:13,826
and many of them agreed with me.

111
00:08:15,953 --> 00:08:17,163
It's pretty quiet so far.

112
00:08:17,246 --> 00:08:19,999
It won't last long.
It'll get noisy very soon.

113
00:08:21,459 --> 00:08:25,213
Assemblyman Lee Seong-min,
you may go next.

114
00:08:27,215 --> 00:08:29,967
I'm Assemblyman Lee Seong-min,
a nonpartisan.

115
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:33,137
First, I'd like to mention something
regarding the submitted materials.

116
00:08:33,221 --> 00:08:35,640
We requested documents
regarding the social groups

117
00:08:35,723 --> 00:08:38,559
and organizations you were part of
during your tenure as a prosecutor,

118
00:08:38,643 --> 00:08:42,104
but we were told they can't be submitted
as they're considered personal matters.

119
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:45,274
I think such documents are crucial
in determining your eligibility.

120
00:08:45,358 --> 00:08:48,694
We did our best to submit
everything that you requested.

121
00:08:49,278 --> 00:08:50,863
If there is anything that's missing,

122
00:08:50,947 --> 00:08:53,449
I'll answer whatever questions
you may have, right here.

123
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:54,909
That won't suffice.

124
00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:56,494
I'd like those documents immediately.

125
00:08:57,078 --> 00:08:59,455
Please submit them before noon.

126
00:09:03,209 --> 00:09:04,585
Chairperson Lee, please tell him.

127
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:06,504
He is clearly unprepared.

128
00:09:06,587 --> 00:09:08,214
This will set a bad precedent.

129
00:09:08,297 --> 00:09:11,133
Mr. Song, would you be able
to submit all the requested materials?

130
00:09:12,134 --> 00:09:13,469
Yes, I will submit them.

131
00:09:14,887 --> 00:09:17,431
You just made a promise
before the people of this country,

132
00:09:17,515 --> 00:09:19,058
so I trust that you will submit them.

133
00:09:19,141 --> 00:09:21,352
Yes, sure.

134
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:25,606
I'll explain why it's important. When
a new Minister of Justice is appointed,

135
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:27,608
all the corporations
change their law firms

136
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:32,154
to the ones where those who are acquainted
with the new minister.

137
00:09:32,238 --> 00:09:34,699
That is why I believe it's important
to find out

138
00:09:34,782 --> 00:09:36,784
who aligns interests with the candidate.

139
00:09:37,368 --> 00:09:39,829
-Am I wrong?
-I agree.

140
00:09:40,371 --> 00:09:42,123
And that being said,

141
00:09:42,206 --> 00:09:45,543
I'm sure you're aware of
the recent conveyor belt accident

142
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:47,795
at Joojin Constructions,
a subsidiary of Joojin Chemical.

143
00:09:47,878 --> 00:09:48,921
Yes, I am.

144
00:09:49,338 --> 00:09:52,967
It was a truly unfortunate accident.

145
00:09:53,050 --> 00:09:55,177
From what I know,
you and Mr. Lee Chang-jin,

146
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:57,471
the CEO of Joojin Chemical,
are very close. Am I right?

147
00:09:57,555 --> 00:10:00,224
Yes. We met at an entrepreneurs' forum,

148
00:10:00,308 --> 00:10:02,643
and we're still quite close.

149
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:06,272
The documents you submitted
tell us how close the two of you are,

150
00:10:06,355 --> 00:10:07,648
so you probably can't deny it.

151
00:10:07,732 --> 00:10:09,317
When you were a prosecutor,

152
00:10:09,734 --> 00:10:12,528
you handled five cases
related to Mr. Lee Chang-jin,

153
00:10:13,029 --> 00:10:16,073
and he was acquitted of all charges.

154
00:10:16,782 --> 00:10:20,578
Mr. Lee did apologize
for the unfortunate accident,

155
00:10:20,661 --> 00:10:23,539
but he's completely ignoring
the aftermath of the accident.

156
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:26,167
Isn't this because he's counting on
his friendship with you?

157
00:10:27,251 --> 00:10:29,295
Let me say this again.

158
00:10:29,378 --> 00:10:32,548
Mr. Lee Chang-jin
is my personal acquaintance,

159
00:10:33,132 --> 00:10:35,426
but I've never helped him benefit
or profit in any way.

160
00:10:36,218 --> 00:10:39,930
However, some unsavory deeds

161
00:10:40,514 --> 00:10:42,558
recently came to my knowledge.

162
00:10:47,271 --> 00:10:48,272
What are they?

163
00:10:48,856 --> 00:10:50,775
I recently found out

164
00:10:51,359 --> 00:10:54,153
about some unsavory transactions
between Mr. Lee

165
00:10:54,236 --> 00:10:57,198
and one of my closest aides,
who has been meeting him personally.

166
00:10:57,281 --> 00:10:59,367
It only came to my knowledge recently.

167
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:00,576
Please be more specific.

168
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:03,204
Who is that person?

169
00:11:03,412 --> 00:11:08,167
I do not think it's appropriate
to disclose his name here, but...

170
00:11:09,794 --> 00:11:13,464
Since all of you want to know who it is,
I will tell you.

171
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:18,678
I'm ashamed to say this,

172
00:11:19,053 --> 00:11:21,639
but it's my chief of staff,
Mr. Jang Tae-jun.

173
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:27,103
What? What's he talking about?

174
00:11:40,282 --> 00:11:42,952
Oh, dear. Jang Tae-jun is in deep shit.

175
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,422
Ms. Kang.

176
00:11:54,505 --> 00:11:57,258
He wants the hearing
to be all about Mr. Jang,

177
00:11:57,341 --> 00:11:59,719
not about his eligibility
to be Minister of Justice.

178
00:12:04,932 --> 00:12:06,642
The number you have dialed is not...

179
00:12:07,143 --> 00:12:08,436
Gosh, why isn't he picking up?

180
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,357
Mr. Jang!

181
00:12:13,858 --> 00:12:16,777
Were you aware that Mr. Lee and Mr. Jang

182
00:12:16,861 --> 00:12:19,321
had been meeting privately?

183
00:12:22,116 --> 00:12:23,451
I only found out recently.

184
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:25,202
According to a report we received,

185
00:12:25,286 --> 00:12:27,288
Mr. Jang threatened Mr. Lee using the fact

186
00:12:27,371 --> 00:12:29,665
that he works for you
to illegally obtain stock information

187
00:12:29,749 --> 00:12:32,168
and even asked for a director position.

188
00:12:32,251 --> 00:12:33,419
Is it true?

189
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:38,174
Yes, as far as I know.

190
00:12:38,257 --> 00:12:41,469
Chairperson Lee, we'll have to
find out more about this allegation.

191
00:12:41,552 --> 00:12:44,513
We'd like Mr. Lee Chang-jin
to take the witness stand.

192
00:12:44,597 --> 00:12:46,348
Please proceed.

193
00:12:49,101 --> 00:12:49,935
What is happening?

194
00:12:50,019 --> 00:12:52,104
Mr. Song wants to use me
to make sure he is appointed.

195
00:12:52,688 --> 00:12:54,482
He's trying to put all the blame on me.

196
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:57,401
If Lee Chang-jin testifies against me,
I'll be finished.

197
00:12:57,777 --> 00:12:59,779
But it'd only be words without evidence--

198
00:12:59,862 --> 00:13:01,572
Evidence can be crafted.

199
00:13:02,239 --> 00:13:03,741
He's so close to becoming a minister.

200
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:06,619
Everyone in the prosecution is
at his disposal. He has the power.

201
00:13:07,745 --> 00:13:09,413
Destroy all the documents I have.

202
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:11,165
Who knows what he'll use?

203
00:13:12,124 --> 00:13:13,709
Why don't we get help

204
00:13:13,793 --> 00:13:15,961
from Assemblyman Lee
to prepare materials for refutation?

205
00:13:16,045 --> 00:13:17,546
We have time until the afternoon.

206
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:19,465
The confirmation hearing
will be adjourned.

207
00:13:20,090 --> 00:13:20,925
What?

208
00:13:22,051 --> 00:13:23,469
Before taking the oath,

209
00:13:23,552 --> 00:13:26,472
please note that this part of the hearing
will not be open to the public

210
00:13:26,555 --> 00:13:29,600
according to Article 14
of the Personnel Hearing Act.

211
00:13:29,683 --> 00:13:31,060
-What?
-Can they do that?

212
00:13:31,143 --> 00:13:35,231
All reporters, note that no photography
or recording is allowed from here on.

213
00:13:35,314 --> 00:13:37,483
It's not open to the public?
What do you mean?

214
00:13:37,566 --> 00:13:40,152
According to Article 14.3
of the Personnel Hearing Act--

215
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:43,072
I think this is crucial in determining
the candidate's eligibility.

216
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:44,490
Why must we go off-the-record?

217
00:13:44,573 --> 00:13:46,826
"Because information
about a legitimate financial

218
00:13:46,909 --> 00:13:50,329
or commercial transaction of an enterprise
or an individual is likely to be--"

219
00:13:50,412 --> 00:13:51,997
Why are you doing this all of a sudden?

220
00:13:52,122 --> 00:13:53,624
Are you trying to protect him?

221
00:13:53,707 --> 00:13:56,168
Have we ever obeyed Article 14
of the Act?

222
00:13:56,252 --> 00:13:58,963
Are you saying
we can completely ignore it, then?

223
00:13:59,046 --> 00:14:01,423
-We're going by the law.
-This is unprecedented.

224
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:04,802
-You're protecting him, aren't you?
-Look, watch what you say!

225
00:14:13,644 --> 00:14:15,187
Quiet down, please.

226
00:14:16,564 --> 00:14:19,149
He brought Mr. Lee to make sure
the hearing ends up being adjourned.

227
00:14:20,609 --> 00:14:23,821
If it's adjourned only after he brings up
the allegations about me...

228
00:14:23,904 --> 00:14:26,031
That way, all the suspicions
about him will dissipate,

229
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:28,659
and people will only talk about you.

230
00:14:31,996 --> 00:14:34,039
-Come on.
-Sir, please reconsider this.

231
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:36,083
Prior to becoming
a Minister of Justice nominee...

232
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:39,086
-When did you find out about Mr. Jang?
-Have you been overlooking it?

233
00:14:39,169 --> 00:14:40,170
Tell us more.

234
00:14:40,254 --> 00:14:43,924
I only found out about it while preparing
for my confirmation hearing.

235
00:14:44,008 --> 00:14:48,721
I do not know any details
about the transactions between them.

236
00:14:48,804 --> 00:14:51,015
But as the protector of the Constitution,

237
00:14:51,181 --> 00:14:55,019
I believe that I mustn't side with him
even if he's my chief of staff.

238
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:57,479
If I'm appointed Minister of Justice,

239
00:14:57,563 --> 00:15:01,317
I'll be sure to get to the bottom of this.

240
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:04,320
The Seoul Western Prosecutor's Office
is already looking into the case.

241
00:15:04,987 --> 00:15:08,574
This will pain me for a while.
However, I promise

242
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:11,035
that I will faithfully cooperate
with the investigation.

243
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:15,623
Once again, I'd like to sincerely
apologize to the people of this country.

244
00:15:16,624 --> 00:15:18,125
Please say a few more words.

245
00:15:18,208 --> 00:15:20,628
-Did you really not know?
-How do you feel now?

246
00:15:20,711 --> 00:15:22,796
-Please tell us more.
-Another comment, please.

247
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:25,090
-Sir, please tell us.
-Sir.

248
00:15:25,674 --> 00:15:27,384
Did you really not know about it?

249
00:15:33,849 --> 00:15:35,100
Hurry up already!

250
00:15:39,146 --> 00:15:40,439
Mr. Jang, what is happening?

251
00:15:56,997 --> 00:15:59,667
Mr. Jang Tae-jun, it's been a while.

252
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:06,048
ARREST WARRANT

253
00:16:11,762 --> 00:16:13,847
-Gosh, what is happening?
-What's going on?

254
00:16:14,556 --> 00:16:15,933
Is it true?

255
00:16:17,184 --> 00:16:18,394
My gosh, it must be true.

256
00:16:32,324 --> 00:16:34,201
I'm Prosecutor Seo Hyeong-cheol.

257
00:16:38,163 --> 00:16:39,456
Is this really necessary?

258
00:16:39,790 --> 00:16:43,168
We were a family. I should at least
buy him a meal before I send him off.

259
00:16:44,086 --> 00:16:45,462
Sure. That will be fine, sir.

260
00:16:48,882 --> 00:16:49,717
Let's go.

261
00:17:02,521 --> 00:17:05,482
I'm so hungry from being pestered
by everyone since this morning.

262
00:17:06,066 --> 00:17:07,901
Eat up.
It won't taste good when it gets cold.

263
00:17:10,571 --> 00:17:12,698
What good will it do
if both of us fall into the water?

264
00:17:12,781 --> 00:17:15,617
At least one of us should be standing
to help the other one get out.

265
00:17:18,328 --> 00:17:19,496
Don't take this to heart.

266
00:17:19,580 --> 00:17:21,665
I told you
when you first joined my office.

267
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:23,625
When I'm appointed as a minister,

268
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:26,003
my district will be all yours.

269
00:17:27,296 --> 00:17:30,007
We don't even need to wait
until the legislative election.

270
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:33,510
The by-election is just around the corner,
but the legislative election is next year.

271
00:17:34,803 --> 00:17:36,013
If I'm appointed,

272
00:17:36,096 --> 00:17:38,807
I'll give up my seat
in the Assembly right away.

273
00:17:38,891 --> 00:17:42,144
Then Uigwang City
will need to elect my replacement

274
00:17:42,227 --> 00:17:43,520
in the by-election.

275
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:47,733
Are you saying you'll grant me
the nomination rights?

276
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:49,902
Who else, if not you?

277
00:17:51,111 --> 00:17:51,945
Goodness.

278
00:17:55,824 --> 00:17:58,410
And as for the allegations
that were brought up at the hearing...

279
00:17:58,494 --> 00:18:01,080
As soon as I'm appointed
Minister of Justice...

280
00:18:01,163 --> 00:18:03,248
You see these conch shells?

281
00:18:03,332 --> 00:18:08,087
They'll dissipate like snails
crawling back into their shells.

282
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:10,631
It'll be just for a day or two.

283
00:18:10,714 --> 00:18:13,258
I've already talked to everyone
in the prosecution.

284
00:18:13,342 --> 00:18:16,011
So just go with them
and let them ask you a few questions.

285
00:18:16,595 --> 00:18:18,138
It's just a formality.

286
00:18:18,639 --> 00:18:19,807
You understand, right?

287
00:18:24,436 --> 00:18:26,772
Goodness, what's there to hesitate?

288
00:18:26,855 --> 00:18:28,857
The table is set,
so all you have to do is eat.

289
00:18:29,274 --> 00:18:30,317
Your soup is getting cold.

290
00:18:41,328 --> 00:18:43,038
How should we handle this, sir?

291
00:18:43,122 --> 00:18:45,749
Should we let him go
after interviewing him as a witness? Or...

292
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:48,210
A viper mustn't be let loose.

293
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:50,838
We need to make sure
this won't backfire on Mr. Lee,

294
00:18:50,921 --> 00:18:53,257
so see what you can do
to get an arrest warrant issued.

295
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:56,635
Insider trading and graft.

296
00:18:57,469 --> 00:19:00,139
-Five years should be good enough.
-Understood, sir.

297
00:19:34,798 --> 00:19:36,216
Come with us.

298
00:20:11,376 --> 00:20:12,711
-Jang Tae-jun bolted.
-What?

299
00:20:13,420 --> 00:20:15,297
-Put out an APB now.
-Yes, sir.

300
00:20:16,381 --> 00:20:17,633
Hey, start the car!

301
00:20:21,011 --> 00:20:23,388
I was going to send him off
on a good note.

302
00:20:23,472 --> 00:20:26,642
He's making trouble to the end.

303
00:20:27,643 --> 00:20:30,270
-Tell Won-sik to come back.
-Yes, sir.

304
00:20:30,354 --> 00:20:32,397
SEONGJIN CITY DAEHAN PARTY COMMITTEE

305
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:35,984
What happened to you?

306
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:41,698
I was bitten by a viper.

307
00:20:42,199 --> 00:20:43,325
What do you want to know?

308
00:20:45,369 --> 00:20:46,745
Last legislative election...

309
00:20:46,828 --> 00:20:49,373
Are you sure that Lee Seong-min
was the one who exposed

310
00:20:49,456 --> 00:20:50,874
your bribery case?

311
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:54,378
I had to withdraw from the race
because of that.

312
00:20:54,836 --> 00:20:56,546
And he was elected.
Do you need more proof?

313
00:20:56,630 --> 00:20:59,216
The organization that was supporting me
switched to him, too.

314
00:20:59,299 --> 00:21:00,425
Who else could it be?

315
00:21:02,594 --> 00:21:04,096
But how do you think he found out?

316
00:21:05,097 --> 00:21:07,557
Beats me.
That's what I'd like to know, too.

317
00:21:07,975 --> 00:21:10,602
There's no way he could've known about it
unless it came from our side.

318
00:21:11,937 --> 00:21:14,064
Who was the detective on the case?

319
00:21:15,190 --> 00:21:16,858
His name is Lee Hyeong-bae.

320
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:19,486
He's a detective
at Seongjin Police Agency.

321
00:21:19,569 --> 00:21:22,614
He got promoted after my case
and was transferred to Seoul.

322
00:21:24,283 --> 00:21:27,911
Detective Lee Hyeong-bae.

323
00:21:40,966 --> 00:21:42,301
What's your plan now?

324
00:21:44,177 --> 00:21:46,388
I should get off the tiger's back.

325
00:21:48,348 --> 00:21:49,975
Will Mr. Song let you?

326
00:21:50,058 --> 00:21:53,520
I'll bite off the tiger's neck
if I have to.

327
00:21:55,355 --> 00:21:56,523
How can I help?

328
00:21:59,818 --> 00:22:01,153
See you at the park.

329
00:22:02,696 --> 00:22:04,948
Gather information
on Mr. Song's first election.

330
00:22:05,032 --> 00:22:07,200
-We'll find something.
-Okay.

331
00:22:08,368 --> 00:22:09,202
I need your help.

332
00:22:18,295 --> 00:22:21,673
Suspicions that Assemblyman Song's
chief of staff Mr. Jang

333
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:23,842
threatened Lee Chang-jin,

334
00:22:23,925 --> 00:22:26,636
the CEO of Joojin Chemical,
to gain privileges have been brought up

335
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:29,681
at Assemblyman Song's confirmation
hearing for the Minister of Justice today.

336
00:22:30,223 --> 00:22:32,142
Mr. Jang even mobilized
his father to disrupt

337
00:22:32,225 --> 00:22:33,894
Assemblyman Lee Seong-min's office

338
00:22:33,977 --> 00:22:36,104
that was in charge
of the redevelopment project.

339
00:22:36,188 --> 00:22:38,315
It's been confirmed
that he has been also involved in

340
00:22:38,398 --> 00:22:40,192
Uigwang's and Seongjin's
redevelopment project.

341
00:22:40,275 --> 00:22:42,778
The authority has put out an APB
on Mr. Jang.

342
00:22:42,861 --> 00:22:45,238
Prosecutor Seo from the Western
Prosecutor's Office is in charge.

343
00:22:45,906 --> 00:22:48,492
Prosecutor Seo is one
of Mr. Jo's connections.

344
00:22:49,576 --> 00:22:52,662
Mr. Jo told me to step back
from the hearing.

345
00:22:52,996 --> 00:22:54,790
I'm sure he's siding with Mr. Song now.

346
00:22:56,041 --> 00:22:59,795
Bringing in Mr. Lee as a witness
was all part of their plan.

347
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:02,339
He was planning
to pin everything on Tae-jun.

348
00:23:03,298 --> 00:23:04,716
Will the hearing reconvene?

349
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:06,051
Even if it does,

350
00:23:06,134 --> 00:23:08,387
we don't have anything
we can use against Mr. Song.

351
00:23:09,930 --> 00:23:11,848
What about the additional materials
from Mr. Song?

352
00:23:11,932 --> 00:23:14,726
I did receive them,
but I didn't find anything useful.

353
00:23:16,770 --> 00:23:18,230
If the hearing ends like this,

354
00:23:18,313 --> 00:23:20,649
Mr. Song will be appointed
as the Minister of Justice.

355
00:23:20,732 --> 00:23:24,194
If that happens,
we won't be able to save Tae-jun.

356
00:23:30,742 --> 00:23:33,286
Mr. Lee, you should prepare
for the afternoon session for now.

357
00:23:33,370 --> 00:23:35,455
I'll call Mr. Jang.

358
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:38,291
Okay.

359
00:23:43,171 --> 00:23:44,256
UIGWANG CITY LIBRARY

360
00:23:58,270 --> 00:24:01,606
CHANGES IN INDUSTRIAL ACCIDENTS
REPORTING SYSTEM

361
00:24:08,029 --> 00:24:09,156
Don't give up.

362
00:24:09,239 --> 00:24:10,574
Mr. Han,

363
00:24:11,575 --> 00:24:14,911
you must keep going
for the sake of Yu Jin-su's grandmother.

364
00:24:15,412 --> 00:24:18,623
And it doesn't have to be
at Mr. Song's office.

365
00:24:18,707 --> 00:24:20,542
As long as you stick to your beliefs,

366
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:23,211
I'm sure you'll find a place
where you can work at.

367
00:24:27,007 --> 00:24:27,883
CIVIL SERVICE EXAM PREP

368
00:24:39,311 --> 00:24:40,770
No coffee today?

369
00:24:42,439 --> 00:24:44,483
I'll buy you double shot coffee next time.

370
00:24:45,275 --> 00:24:48,153
Hey, the prosecution is going berserk,
trying to arrest you.

371
00:24:48,236 --> 00:24:50,655
But you're still making jokes
and haven't lost your cool yet.

372
00:24:53,241 --> 00:24:56,036
-Is that what I requested?
-Well, I didn't find much on Mr. Song.

373
00:24:56,119 --> 00:24:58,580
He must've cleaned up well. It's spotless.

374
00:24:58,663 --> 00:25:01,458
This is all there's left to his dirt.

375
00:25:07,631 --> 00:25:10,759
Let's stop here.
He's too big of a fish for us to catch.

376
00:25:10,842 --> 00:25:13,220
I'll make sure this doesn't affect you.
Don't worry.

377
00:25:16,056 --> 00:25:18,850
I can take care of myself.
Just take care of yourself.

378
00:25:19,351 --> 00:25:20,477
Bye.

379
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:45,502
-Hello.
-It's me.

380
00:25:48,922 --> 00:25:49,881
Where are you?

381
00:25:52,676 --> 00:25:53,843
I'll head over there.

382
00:25:57,013 --> 00:25:59,307
While the confirmation hearing

383
00:25:59,391 --> 00:26:01,434
of Assemblyman Song Hui-seop
is in full swing,

384
00:26:01,518 --> 00:26:04,145
the suspicion that Mr. Jang,
Assemblyman Song's chief of staff,

385
00:26:04,229 --> 00:26:06,773
threatened the CEO
of Joojin Chemical, Lee Chang-jin,

386
00:26:06,856 --> 00:26:09,276
to gain numerous privileges
has been brought up.

387
00:26:09,359 --> 00:26:10,819
-Mr. Jang.
-The prosecution

388
00:26:10,902 --> 00:26:12,237
has issued an APB on Mr. Jang

389
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:14,739
-and has launched an investigation on him.
-Ms. Yun.

390
00:26:15,282 --> 00:26:17,993
Did you hear?
They issued an APB on Mr. Jang.

391
00:26:18,827 --> 00:26:20,370
Did Mr. Jang really do something wrong?

392
00:26:21,162 --> 00:26:23,123
I don't have the faintest idea
of what's happening.

393
00:26:23,206 --> 00:26:24,457
Mr. Oh and Mr. Jang aren't here.

394
00:26:24,541 --> 00:26:26,585
Will I have to help Mr. Song
for the hearing?

395
00:26:29,546 --> 00:26:30,422
You're here.

396
00:26:31,506 --> 00:26:34,175
-Has Tae-jun called?
-No, he hasn't.

397
00:26:36,219 --> 00:26:37,345
No, he hasn't.

398
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:40,390
Report to me if he calls.

399
00:26:40,932 --> 00:26:41,766
Yes, sir.

400
00:26:52,652 --> 00:26:56,156
I heard the prosecution
put out an APB on you. What's your plan?

401
00:26:57,907 --> 00:27:00,452
Just go to the prosecutor's office.
I'll help you.

402
00:27:00,535 --> 00:27:02,245
You can't be on the run forever.

403
00:27:02,329 --> 00:27:05,415
Once I go in, my life will be over.

404
00:27:05,498 --> 00:27:08,877
Even so, Tae-jun,
if Mr. Song's hearing reconvenes,

405
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:11,212
Assemblyman Lee won't be able
to stop him by himself.

406
00:27:12,380 --> 00:27:13,798
I'm not going after Mr. Song.

407
00:27:14,382 --> 00:27:15,967
I must go after someone more powerful.

408
00:27:17,552 --> 00:27:19,429
The chairman of Youngil Group,
Sung Yeong-gi.

409
00:27:20,096 --> 00:27:22,515
Is there anything I should know
regarding Youngil Group?

410
00:27:22,599 --> 00:27:23,808
I told you not to worry!

411
00:27:24,392 --> 00:27:25,977
When Mr. Song worked as a prosecutor,

412
00:27:26,061 --> 00:27:28,021
he covered up Youngil Group's
slush fund case.

413
00:27:28,104 --> 00:27:31,441
That's how he got into politics.
Youngil Group is his weak point right now.

414
00:27:31,524 --> 00:27:35,153
I know that. But we didn't find
a single trace of his involvement

415
00:27:35,236 --> 00:27:37,739
from the complete enumeration
of the borrowed-name bank accounts.

416
00:27:40,158 --> 00:27:41,660
This will help.

417
00:27:50,877 --> 00:27:52,879
How did the meeting
with the administrator go?

418
00:27:54,005 --> 00:27:57,634
Mr. Lee Chang-jin
will be the last witness at the hearing.

419
00:27:57,717 --> 00:28:00,679
It's been settled that the hearing
will start with the rest of the questions.

420
00:28:01,096 --> 00:28:04,265
When the hearing resumes this afternoon,
you'll be asked some basic questions.

421
00:28:04,349 --> 00:28:06,351
Consider this a formality

422
00:28:06,434 --> 00:28:08,353
and answer the questions accordingly.

423
00:28:08,853 --> 00:28:09,854
What about Lee Seong-min?

424
00:28:09,938 --> 00:28:13,316
Don't worry. We've already changed
the order of his speaking time.

425
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:15,068
And Assemblyman Ahn will ask...

426
00:28:15,151 --> 00:28:18,238
questions Assemblyman Lee
was planning to ask before his turn.

427
00:28:18,488 --> 00:28:21,282
Until we resume, please get some rest.

428
00:28:23,535 --> 00:28:25,537
Why do you still look concerned?

429
00:28:25,620 --> 00:28:27,914
Aren't things going well
according to the plan?

430
00:28:29,541 --> 00:28:32,585
Thinking of that punk Jang Tae-jun
is bothering me.

431
00:28:34,546 --> 00:28:38,049
You and he are no longer in the same boat.
What can he do?

432
00:28:38,133 --> 00:28:40,468
Both prosecutors are involved now.

433
00:28:40,552 --> 00:28:43,304
I'm sure they will have him
in custody soon.

434
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:45,014
Please rest up for the time being.

435
00:28:47,684 --> 00:28:49,728
They suddenly changed
the order of your speaking time.

436
00:28:49,853 --> 00:28:52,188
They are trying to stop you
from asking these questions.

437
00:28:57,777 --> 00:29:00,864
Mr. Song will end up becoming
the Minister of Justice,

438
00:29:01,239 --> 00:29:03,324
so let's not provoke him
and end the hearing--

439
00:29:03,408 --> 00:29:04,951
Even if the hearing ends in his favor,

440
00:29:05,034 --> 00:29:07,954
Mr. Song won't let this slide.

441
00:29:08,163 --> 00:29:10,457
He'll put more pressure on us
from a more powerful position.

442
00:29:10,540 --> 00:29:12,375
But there's nothing we can do now.

443
00:29:13,460 --> 00:29:14,335
Let's start with this.

444
00:29:18,965 --> 00:29:21,342
The honorary chairman of Youngil Group,
Sung Yeong-gi.

445
00:29:21,426 --> 00:29:24,137
During the slush fund case,
he divided the group and stepped back

446
00:29:24,220 --> 00:29:25,555
as the honorary chairman.

447
00:29:25,638 --> 00:29:28,099
That's when
Youngil Constructions' value dropped

448
00:29:28,475 --> 00:29:30,727
and he sold it to Mr. Lee
of Joojin Chemical.

449
00:29:30,810 --> 00:29:32,395
Then it became Joojin Constructions.

450
00:29:32,771 --> 00:29:35,899
Mr. Lee bought a company
that was crumbling down

451
00:29:35,982 --> 00:29:39,360
and has succeeded in growing the company.

452
00:29:39,444 --> 00:29:42,155
This was possible
because he had an unexpected investor.

453
00:29:42,238 --> 00:29:45,408
LD Global from Singapore
invested in his company.

454
00:29:45,492 --> 00:29:50,163
The biggest shareholder with 33%
of Joojin Constructions' shares.

455
00:29:51,873 --> 00:29:54,793
LD Global... Is that a paper company?

456
00:29:55,376 --> 00:29:58,129
Yes, it only exists on paper.

457
00:29:58,213 --> 00:30:01,633
The real owner of LD Global
is Chairman Sung Yeong-gi.

458
00:30:03,384 --> 00:30:06,679
That means Lee Chang-jin
is only a figurehead.

459
00:30:06,763 --> 00:30:08,348
The real owner of Joojin Constructions

460
00:30:08,431 --> 00:30:10,683
is Sung Yeong-gi,
the honorary chairman of Youngil Group.

461
00:30:10,767 --> 00:30:12,894
Yes, when Mr. Song worked as a prosecutor,

462
00:30:12,977 --> 00:30:16,105
he didn't include any of this
in his report and ignored evidence.

463
00:30:16,189 --> 00:30:18,149
And with the funds
he received from Youngil Group,

464
00:30:18,233 --> 00:30:19,484
he got into politics.

465
00:30:19,567 --> 00:30:20,944
And I'm pretty sure the fund came

466
00:30:21,027 --> 00:30:23,488
from the slush fund
he created with the paper company.

467
00:30:23,571 --> 00:30:26,282
I think he set up the slush fund
by selling off the shares

468
00:30:26,366 --> 00:30:28,034
of LD Global.

469
00:30:28,117 --> 00:30:29,702
And the fund is being used to lobby

470
00:30:29,786 --> 00:30:31,579
Mr. Song and Samil Association.

471
00:30:33,873 --> 00:30:36,709
Request the Financial Intelligence Unit
for the overseas transaction.

472
00:30:36,793 --> 00:30:39,087
Once we trace the transfer
of the assets overseas,

473
00:30:39,170 --> 00:30:40,505
we can find the flow of the funds

474
00:30:40,588 --> 00:30:44,092
It will take over a month to receive
such information from the FIU.

475
00:30:44,676 --> 00:30:45,677
Meanwhile,

476
00:30:45,760 --> 00:30:48,930
we must find a connection
between Mr. Song and Chairman Sung.

477
00:30:49,013 --> 00:30:51,516
We don't have much time left.
Where can we find it?

478
00:30:51,599 --> 00:30:54,686
When LD Global increased the capital
by issuing new stocks on KOSDAQ,

479
00:30:54,769 --> 00:30:57,438
an accounting firm was in charge
of evaluating the company's value.

480
00:30:58,773 --> 00:30:59,899
It's Naon Accounting.

481
00:31:00,942 --> 00:31:02,235
Naon Accounting...

482
00:31:03,653 --> 00:31:06,573
They were once investigated
for fraudulent accounting and tax evasion.

483
00:31:06,656 --> 00:31:09,033
And Mr. Song was
the prosecutor in charge again.

484
00:31:09,117 --> 00:31:10,827
And of course, charges were cleared.

485
00:31:10,910 --> 00:31:13,538
I'm sure the firm has
some relevant files left.

486
00:31:14,122 --> 00:31:15,832
But do you think
they'll hand over the files?

487
00:31:17,166 --> 00:31:20,169
Mr. Jang will take care of it.

488
00:31:26,175 --> 00:31:28,219
NAON ACCOUNTING

489
00:31:34,183 --> 00:31:35,643
Sir, you have a visitor.

490
00:31:35,727 --> 00:31:37,270
Is that so? Okay.

491
00:31:40,648 --> 00:31:42,358
So you're interested
in making investments?

492
00:31:42,442 --> 00:31:43,776
Yes.

493
00:31:43,860 --> 00:31:45,695
I'm Oh Yong-su, the CEO of the firm.

494
00:31:50,617 --> 00:31:52,785
What kind of companies
are you interested in?

495
00:31:54,037 --> 00:31:55,246
LD Global.

496
00:31:59,584 --> 00:32:00,710
Where are you from?

497
00:32:01,085 --> 00:32:02,045
Aren't you being investigated

498
00:32:02,128 --> 00:32:04,714
by Seoul Metropolitan Police Agency
on fraud charges?

499
00:32:07,258 --> 00:32:11,095
Who are you? Get out of here quietly
before I call the police.

500
00:32:15,016 --> 00:32:17,101
What do you think you're doing now?

501
00:32:18,019 --> 00:32:19,145
We've arrived.

502
00:32:21,105 --> 00:32:24,317
-Hey, call the police.
-There's no need.

503
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:26,653
-They are already here.
-Come in quickly.

504
00:32:28,112 --> 00:32:29,405
What is this about?

505
00:32:29,489 --> 00:32:32,283
We're from Seoul Metropolitan
Police Agency. Please cooperate with us.

506
00:32:32,367 --> 00:32:33,284
Start the search.

507
00:32:34,577 --> 00:32:37,038
-What are you doing?
-I'm giving you a chance to choose.

508
00:32:37,121 --> 00:32:39,374
It'll be only three years in prison
and two years on probation

509
00:32:39,457 --> 00:32:40,583
for a simple fraud charge.

510
00:32:40,667 --> 00:32:43,753
But you'll serve ten years max
for fraudulent accounting and tax evasion.

511
00:32:46,923 --> 00:32:48,007
What is it that you want?

512
00:32:48,341 --> 00:32:50,134
LD Global's ledger.

513
00:32:50,718 --> 00:32:52,679
I think that will be enough
to save your life.

514
00:32:59,477 --> 00:33:00,853
-Mr. Go.
-Yes.

515
00:33:00,937 --> 00:33:01,896
-Here you go.
-Thanks.

516
00:33:04,107 --> 00:33:05,358
Ms. Kang.

517
00:33:12,281 --> 00:33:13,700
This isn't enough,

518
00:33:13,783 --> 00:33:15,910
but you'll be able to pressure
Mr. Song with this.

519
00:33:15,994 --> 00:33:18,538
Nonetheless, he'll keep denying
any connections with Youngil Group.

520
00:33:18,621 --> 00:33:20,999
Even so, it will leave suspicions.

521
00:33:21,624 --> 00:33:22,709
If he can't resolve them,

522
00:33:22,792 --> 00:33:25,461
getting the hearing report approved
will be difficult.

523
00:33:27,171 --> 00:33:29,716
Mr. Lee, the hearing will reconvene soon.

524
00:33:34,679 --> 00:33:36,431
Let's try everything we can.

525
00:33:45,898 --> 00:33:47,650
NOMINEE SONG HUI-SEOP'S HEARING

526
00:33:50,737 --> 00:33:53,072
MINISTER OF JUSTICE NOMINEE

527
00:34:15,261 --> 00:34:17,346
Mr. Song,
didn't you investigate Youngil Group

528
00:34:17,430 --> 00:34:19,557
regarding their slush fund
when you were a prosecutor?

529
00:34:20,141 --> 00:34:21,184
That's correct.

530
00:34:21,267 --> 00:34:24,228
After the investigation, when some of
Youngil Group's companies were divided,

531
00:34:24,854 --> 00:34:26,355
they sold off a few subsidiaries.

532
00:34:26,439 --> 00:34:28,566
And one of them was Youngil Constructions.

533
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:31,986
Mr. Lee Chang-jin was the one
who bought Youngil Constructions,

534
00:34:32,070 --> 00:34:34,113
which became Joojin Constructions
that we know of now.

535
00:34:34,697 --> 00:34:37,909
This morning, you admitted to being
well-acquainted with Mr. Lee Chang-jin.

536
00:34:38,618 --> 00:34:41,537
By any chance, are you also
well-acquainted with Youngil Group?

537
00:34:42,288 --> 00:34:43,456
You sure jump to conclusions.

538
00:34:43,539 --> 00:34:45,500
I do not know anyone from Youngil Group.

539
00:34:45,583 --> 00:34:46,918
Are you certain?

540
00:34:47,877 --> 00:34:48,920
Yes, I am.

541
00:34:49,504 --> 00:34:50,630
Okay.

542
00:34:51,631 --> 00:34:55,093
Then, have you heard
of a company called LD Global?

543
00:34:56,552 --> 00:34:57,595
No, I have not.

544
00:34:57,678 --> 00:34:58,971
Assemblyman Lee.

545
00:34:59,055 --> 00:35:02,266
Please ask questions
that only concern the nominee.

546
00:35:02,350 --> 00:35:03,434
LD Global is

547
00:35:03,518 --> 00:35:06,437
the biggest shareholder with 33%
of Joojin Constructions' shares.

548
00:35:06,521 --> 00:35:07,772
Surely, you must know that.

549
00:35:09,107 --> 00:35:10,024
No, I don't.

550
00:35:11,734 --> 00:35:13,402
When Mr. Lee and I meet,

551
00:35:14,070 --> 00:35:17,949
we don't discuss anything
that has to do with his business.

552
00:35:18,533 --> 00:35:21,452
Mr. Lee, as your time has run out--

553
00:35:21,536 --> 00:35:23,454
You've met the CEO of LD Global,
haven't you?

554
00:35:23,538 --> 00:35:26,290
-Who's the CEO?
-Turn off his microphone.

555
00:35:26,374 --> 00:35:28,918
You know the connection
between Youngil Group and LD Global.

556
00:35:29,001 --> 00:35:32,171
-Why aren't you answering?
-Time's up.

557
00:35:32,255 --> 00:35:34,549
We'll adjourn for the time being.

558
00:35:48,062 --> 00:35:49,188
How is it going?

559
00:35:49,272 --> 00:35:51,315
-He won't talk.
-It's confidential.

560
00:35:51,399 --> 00:35:53,943
I don't think I can acquire the info
before the hearing is over.

561
00:35:54,527 --> 00:35:55,570
How's the hearing going?

562
00:35:55,653 --> 00:35:57,697
Assemblyman Lee is doing a great job,

563
00:35:57,780 --> 00:35:59,532
