the organization that funded Mr. Lee.

681
00:43:47,458 --> 00:43:48,667
He'll find something for sure.

682
00:43:48,876 --> 00:43:50,919
Let me think.

683
00:43:51,003 --> 00:43:53,005
The legislative election was in March.

684
00:43:53,088 --> 00:43:57,176
That's exactly when Tae-jun left
Assemblyman Lee's election camp

685
00:43:57,259 --> 00:43:59,303
and started working for me.

686
00:43:59,386 --> 00:44:00,387
That's right.

687
00:44:00,929 --> 00:44:02,014
This is so touching.

688
00:44:02,097 --> 00:44:05,184
Tae-jun left the camp
so it won't affect him.

689
00:44:05,267 --> 00:44:06,352
What should I do?

690
00:44:06,435 --> 00:44:10,439
I think this will be enough
to end Tae-jun's career.

691
00:44:11,523 --> 00:44:14,568
It'll be such a waste
to only use this on Tae-jun.

692
00:44:16,362 --> 00:44:18,572
If they're so close with each other,

693
00:44:19,531 --> 00:44:20,783
they should go down together.

694
00:44:24,453 --> 00:44:28,999
I guess we won't be having the meeting
regarding the hearing report tomorrow.

695
00:44:56,151 --> 00:44:57,111
What are you doing here?

696
00:44:57,194 --> 00:44:59,238
It's only right to visit a colleague

697
00:44:59,321 --> 00:45:00,864
when he is being investigated.

698
00:45:05,077 --> 00:45:07,287
I didn't know we were so close.

699
00:45:07,371 --> 00:45:10,040
Hey, we've worked together for four years.

700
00:45:10,124 --> 00:45:12,042
